editorialSummary.text: Intimate, brick-walled eatery & bar with handcrafted cocktails, eclectic small plates & a courtyard.

originalText.text:
Cute and friendly bar. Cozy tables and bar seating. Had a cool, post work or post dinner vibe.

Plenty of wine by the glass options and of course full bar list.

Cute decor. Dark inside so would be a nice date spot as it's not too loud or aggressive late night. Old movies running on projectors on the walls was also unique and something that makes a nice conversation starter.

Staff was nice, though had to be flagged down if you needed them. Even at the bar they never noticed we were out of water or drinks. A bit annoying as it wasn't busy, but I guess the vibe isn't helicopter style, but more like "shout if you need us." Not a problem, just good to know.

My friend goes regularly and loves it.

originalText.text: Such a nice warm atmosphere! You could tell as soon as you walked in, people were enjoying their time chatting and company with each other.  The decor is charming, lighting a little on the darker side but makes the experience :)  our drinks were yummy, well made.  I had the maracuya mama, it was perfectly made!! Perfect mix of sweet and light spice.  Yum!! My hubby had the cool, calm, caliente.  It was also well made, my hubby said it was fine, lol but drank it all. I tasted it and had that smoky mezcal taste. Iâ€™m glad I picked the one I did: Iâ€™m more into sweeter, fresher drinks.   Then our food arrived. I ordered the green pasta, literally it was green.  The creamy sauce needed a little bit of salt. The shrimp was perfectly cooked. The pasta was al dente. My hubby ordered the Steak: 7oz filet mignon, vegetables and fries.  He truly enjoyed his meal.  The meat was cooked right in point, which was medium.  The fries were scrumptious.  Overall nice  restaurant, bar to have a good meal and great drinks!!

originalText.text: Real fun West Side NYC eatery to enjoy a meal.  Throughout the meal, classic old movies from the golden age of Hollywood were shown on various walls.  There were also photos of legendary actors and actresses hanging in the booths.  Oh, and the food is superb.  I started with the tomato soup which was creamy, smooth, and simply divine.  It was served with 3 large pieces of fried bread which enhanced the experience.  I also had the 7 oz filet mignon steak which was just the right size.  It was served with fries and this incredible vegetable medley which was unique and flavorful.  Our server was perfect.  He was friendly, accommodating, yet not overbearing.  He also assisted the other staff in clearing and setting tables.  Overall, a very impressive restaurant, with very reasonable prices.
